.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-SHOW 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-show \- show the selected hunk or a file review
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch show
[\fB\-\-from\fR \fIBATCH\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR [\fIPATH\fR] | \fB\-\-files\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-page\fR \fIPAGES\fR]
[\fB\-\-porcelain\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B show
prints the currently selected hunk. It can also open a page-aware review for
one file, list matching files, or show changes stored in a batch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-from " BATCH
Show changes from
.IR BATCH .
.TP
.B \-\-file
.RI [ PATH ]
Show all changes from one file. If
.I PATH
is omitted, use the selected hunk's file.
.TP
.BI "\-\-files " PATTERN "..."
Show files matched by gitignore-style patterns. Multi-file matches print a
navigational file list and do not select a hidden file for later bare actions.
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Show only the requested display line IDs.
.TP
.BI "\-\-page, \-\-pages " PAGES
Show file-review pages such as
.BR 2 ,
.BR 3-4 ,
or
.BR all .
Requires a single file. Cannot be combined with
.B \-\-line
or
.BR \-\-porcelain .
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Exit silently with status code 0 when a hunk exists and 1 when no hunk exists.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
git-stage-batch show
git-stage-batch show --file src/app.py --page 2
git-stage-batch show --from cleanup --files 'src/**' '!src/vendor/**'
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-include (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-discard (1)
